data.description: A clear, rock bottom creek flows across +/-15 acres of mature Tennessee hardwood forest! An ideal location for a home or cabin, the site offers views through picturesque forest. Conveniently located +/-2 mi. from a public boat launch on the Tennessee River/Kentucky Lake. Electricity available at the paved road frontage. Fishing enthusiasts will delight in the world-class freshwater fishing just a five-minute drive away. For the wildlife lover, this area is also known for its abundant deer and turkey populations! Conveniently located just a five-minute drive from I-40 (Exit 133). With Nashville only one hour away, this location offers both natural beauty and accessibility. All information deemed accurate, but IS-NOT guaranteed by Broker or Seller.
